  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a silver triumph medal commemorating one of the most celebrated military exploits in Dutch history — the **Capture of Breda on 4 March 1590** using the \"Turfschip van Breda\" (Peat Ship of Breda), often compared to the **Trojan Horse**. Approximately 68–75 Dutch and English soldiers under **Charles de Héraugière** hid inside a peat barge, sailed unchecked past Spanish guards into the castle, and captured it at dawn. The medal was struck by order of the States-General just **16 days** after the event (resolution of 20 March 1590), with dies engraved by **Gerard van Bylaer** at the Dordrecht mint. It comes from the personal collection of **Pieter Teyler van der Hulst** — the museum's founder — demonstrating his active interest in Dutch historical medals.",
      "classified_as": [
        {
          "id": "http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300411780",
